He quit his job last year and has spent the previous twelve months travelling the world, visiting countries such as Peru, Japan and Australia.

His reviews include advice about where to buy mosquito repellent, ticket prices and money-saving tips. 

As well as offering suggestions on everything from good hotel rooms and restaurant reviews in exotic and far-flung corners of the globe, Mr Winborn has also reviewed local establishments in his home town.

He said: ‘I always use the site before staying anywhere and I think it is important to give feedback of your experience.

